[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer report indicates a heap-based buffer overflow in the FreeRDP [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodebase. Specifically, an [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte write in the function `Stream_Read` overruns a [0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggered during the processing of a client’s network data in the GCC [0m[1;39m([0m[39mGraphics and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKeyboard Control[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m module.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The buffer was allocated via `calloc` [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize [0m[1;36m992[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in `mcs_new` [0m            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Call stack [0m[1;39m([0m[39moverflow propagation[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `Stream_Read` in winpr/stream.h[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `gcc_read_client_network_data` in libfreerdp/core/gcc.[0m[1;92mc:1875[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. `gcc_read_client_data_blocks` in libfreerdp/core/gcc.[0m[1;92mc:617[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. `gcc_read_conference_create_request` in libfreerdp/core/gcc.[0m[1;92mc:414[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. `mcs_recv_connect_initial` in libfreerdp/core/mcs.[0m[1;92mc:700[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m. `freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_request` in libfreerdp/core/freerdp.[0m[1;92mc:1441[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m7[0m[39m. Fuzzing harness entry [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`test_server` in TestFuzzCoreServer.c[0m[1;39m)[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Important observations:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The overflow occurs precisely at the boundary of the allocated buffer.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The failure is reproducible under the existing fuzzing harness [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The issue is rooted in how data is read from a stream into a finite buffer.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code areas to investigate for a holistic view:[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Stream handling implementation in winpr/stream.h [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparticularly bounds checks [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maround `Stream_Read`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - GCC data parsing routines in libfreerdp/core/gcc.c.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - MCS connection setup in libfreerdp/core/mcs.c and related validation in [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibfreerdp/core/freerdp.c.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Allocation logic in `mcs_new` to verify buffer sizing relative to expected read[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlengths.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Note: The fuzzing harness is an entry point for triggering the overflow and is [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot the root cause.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlevel, wStream* s,[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlevel, wStream* s,[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The AddressSanitizer log points to an [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte write in winpr/stream.h:[0m[1;36m703[0m[39m [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minside Stream_Read, overrunning a heap buffer allocated by calloc in mcs_new [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m992[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - That [0m[1;36m992[0m[39m-byte buffer is mcs->channels, allocated with CHANNEL_MAX_COUNT [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentries [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. [0m[1;36m31[0m[39m × [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mrdpMcsChannel[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow occurs because the client-supplied channel count [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor the number [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof [0m[32m"client network data"[0m[39m channel definitions[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m exceeds CHANNEL_MAX_COUNT, and the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing routine in gcc_read_client_network_data proceeds to read each channel [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefinition—including an [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte field—into mcs->channels without validating that the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcount fits in the allocated array.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In particular, Stream_Read is used to copy fixed-size fields [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., a UINT64 [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandle or name buffer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m from the stream into mcs->channels[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m, and when i == [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mCHANNEL_MAX_COUNT, the writes go past the end of the buffer by exactly [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bytes.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Location & Critical Logic[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The vulnerable code lives in libfreerdp/core/gcc.c within [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgcc_read_client_network_data [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m1875[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m where the routine reads multiple [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchannel definitions based on a count field.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The mcs module’s allocation is fixed to CHANNEL_MAX_COUNT entries. That logic [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmust remain intact to preserve interoperability with other parts of the code.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fix must enforce a strict upper bound on the number of channel definitions[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mread from the stream, matching the CHANNEL_MAX_COUNT used by mcs_new.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Strategy to Fix[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Add explicit bounds checks on channel counts before looping and reading [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchannel definitions:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. In gcc_read_client_network_data [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlibfreerdp/core/gcc.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, locate the code [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat reads the channel count [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlikely a BYTE or UINT8 read into a local variable, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39me.g., channelCount or userDataCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Immediately after reading that count, insert a check:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mchannelCount > CHANNEL_MAX_COUNT[0m[1;39m)[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mWLog_ERR[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTAG, [0m[32m"Too many client channel definitions: %"[0m[39m PRIu8, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchannelCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             return FALSE;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m or appropriate error code to abort parsing[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. This ensures that the subsequent for-loop `for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < channelCount; [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mi++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` cannot index past the allocated array boundaries.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Mirror the same check in any other parsing paths that use a separate “channel[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcount” to read into mcs->channels, for example:[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - In mcs_recv_connect_initial [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlibfreerdp/core/mcs.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, after reading the list[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof user channels to join, verify the read count against CHANNEL_MAX_COUNT in the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame way.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Ensure that if the bounds check fails, the function cleans up appropriately [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mbut does not touch the static mcs->channels pointer beyond returning FALSE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Other[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcleanup is already handled by the caller upon parse failure.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Logic[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - These checks do not alter the structure of the mcs->channels allocation or [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchange functionality for valid inputs [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcount ≤ CHANNEL_MAX_COUNT[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing client messages with a permissible number of channels proceed [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munchanged.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fuzzing logic still drives the same code paths; invalid counts now trigger an [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mearly rejection, avoiding memory corruption.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Side Effects & Mitigations[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A malformed RDP client that reports too many channels will be refused at parse[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtime rather than risking a crash.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Logging the error gives visibility into malformed client data.  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Since the return value changes only for out-of-bound inputs, there is no [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimpact on normal protocol negotiation.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If other parts of code assume a negative return value signals a fatal parse [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merror [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand tear down the connection[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, that remains consistent.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Similar Patterns[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Other parts of the code guard array sizes after reading length fields [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcapability arrays in remaining GCC parsing[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Use those as reference [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimplementations.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Standard practice in FreeRDP is to check length fields against compiled-in [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaximums [0m[1;39m([0m[39msee e.g., the check on the number of MonitorDef structures in [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mupdate_read_multi_monitors[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in libfreerdp/core/fastpath.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Implementation Steps[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Open libfreerdp/core/gcc.c and identify the code around line [0m[1;36m1875[0m[39m where [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclient network data channel definitions are parsed.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Add a pre-loop guard against channelCount > CHANNEL_MAX_COUNT [0m[1;39m([0m[39minclude [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfreerdp/core/mcs.h to get CHANNEL_MAX_COUNT[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Repeat the same guard in libfreerdp/core/mcs.c's mcs_recv_connect_initial [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m700[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m immediately after reading the join-request channel count.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Rebuild and run the existing TestFuzzCoreServer harness; verify that the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer no longer reports heap-buffer-overflow for malformed inputs.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. Run full test suite to ensure no regressions in protocol negotiation.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mmcs_merge_domain_parameters[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&mcs->targetParameters, [0m                   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m&mcs->domainParameters[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Patch [0m[33mResult[0m[39m===[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    #[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m [0m[1;36m0x55a1fd2750b2[0m[39m in main [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/llvm-project/compiler-rt/lib/fuzzer/[0m[95mFuzzerMain.cpp[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m20:10[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    #[0m[1;36m9[0m[39m [0m[1;36m0x7fe96d78e082[0m[39m in __libc_start_main [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[35m/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/[0m[95mlibc.so.6+0x24082[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mBuildId: [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m5792732f783158c66fb4f3756458ca24e46e827d[0m[1;39m)[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: __interceptor_calloc--mcs_new--freerdp_is_valid_mcs_create_request[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mSUMMARY: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/FreeRDP/winpr/include/winpr/[0m[95mstream.h[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m703:3[0m[39m in Stream_Read[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer report indicates a heap-buffer-overflow in FreeRDP’s [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mStream_Read when processing client channel definitions. A proposed patch attempted [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto guard the loops that read channel definitions by first reading a count [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mchannelCount or userChannelCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, checking it against a maximum, and then [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39miterating that many times. When applied, the patch fails to compile: the newly [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintroduced variables [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`channelCount`, `userChannelCount`, `i`, `j`, and `channel`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare not declared, and missing braces cause scoping problems, leading to multiple [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“undeclared identifier” errors in both `gcc.c` and `mcs.c`.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer flags a heap-buffer-overflow during an [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte write at offset[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mequal to the size of a [0m[1;36m992[0m[39m-byte heap allocation.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow occurs in `Stream_Read` within the call chain [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`gcc_read_client_network_data → gcc_read_client_data_blocks → [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgcc_read_conference_create_request`.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The buffer was allocated by `calloc` in `mcs_new`, and the overflow happens as[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclient channel definitions are read without a prior bounds check on the number of [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchannels.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Observations from the ASan Log  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The invalid write address is exactly [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes past the [0m[1;36m992[0m[39m-byte region.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The read loop reads eight bytes for each channel name but the loop count is [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdriven by unvalidated input [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno prior `channelCount` check[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The call originates from a fuzzing harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`TestFuzzCoreServer.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mroot problem is in the channel-definition parsing logic.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `libfreerdp/core/gcc.c`, before reading each channel’s name and options, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe patch reads a `UINT8 channelCount`, compares it to `CHANNEL_MAX_COUNT`, logs [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand returns `FALSE` if exceeded, and then loops `i` from [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m to `channelCount-[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m`.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `libfreerdp/core/mcs.c`, the patch similarly reads `UINT8 [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muserChannelCount`, validates it, logs on overflow, and loops `j` times to call [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`gcc_read_conference_create_request`.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch Application Log and Errors  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `mcs.c`:  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Errors “use of undeclared identifier ‘userChannelCount’” and “undeclared [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentifier ‘j’” indicate missing declarations of those variables.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `gcc.c`:  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Errors “use of undeclared identifier ‘channel’” and “undeclared identifier [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m‘i’” point to scoping issues and missing declarations.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • A warning flags a stray `[0m[35m/[0m[39m*` in a block comment, suggesting misplaced or [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munmatched comment delimiters around the patched region.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The parsing logic in `gcc_read_client_network_data` and [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`gcc_read_conference_create_request` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `gcc.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, specifically how channel [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefinitions and options are read.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The channel‐count fields in the protocol specification—where and how [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`channelCount` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand the user‐channel count in MCS[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are declared and consumed.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The allocation size and layout in `mcs_new` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `mcs.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, verifying that the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mcs->channels` array is sized to accommodate the maximum allowed channels.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensuring all loop counters and count variables are correctly declared and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mscoped, and that comment delimiters do not interfere with code blocks.[0m              [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibfreerdp/core/mcs.[0m[1;92mc:690[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m720[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m690[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn FALSE;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m691[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m692[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* maximumParameters [0m[1;39m([0m[39mDomainParameters[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m693[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mmcs_read_domain_parameters[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, &mcs->maximumParameters[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m694[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn FALSE;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m695[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m696[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mber_read_octet_string_tag[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, &length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ||[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m697[0m[39m:    [0m[39m    [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mStream_CheckAndLogRequiredLength[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTAG, s, length[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m698[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn FALSE;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m699[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m700[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mgcc_read_conference_create_request[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, mcs[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m701[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn FALSE;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m702[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m703[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mmcs_merge_domain_parameters[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&mcs->targetParameters, [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m&mcs->minimumParameters,[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m704[0m[39m:    [0m[39m                                 &mcs->maximumParameters, [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m&mcs->domainParameters[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m705[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn FALSE;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m706[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m707[0m[39m:    [0m[39mreturn [0m[1;35mtpkt_ensure_stream_consumed[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, tlength[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m708[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m709[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m710[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m711[0m[39m: * Write an MCS Connect Initial PDU.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m712[0m[39m: * msdn[0m[1;39m{[0m[39mcc240508[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m713[0m[39m: * @param s stream[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m714[0m[39m: * @param mcs MCS module[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m715[0m[39m: * @param userData GCC Conference Create Request[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m716[0m[39m: *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m717[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m718:B[0m[39mOOL [0m[1;35mmcs_write_connect_initial[0m[1;39m([0m[39mwStream* s, rdpMcs* mcs, wStream* userData[0m[1;39m)[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m719[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m720[0m[39m:    [0m[39msize_t length = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Change the type of `channelCount` in the MCS context to unsigned:[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In libfreerdp/core/mcs.h, replace[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     INT8 channelCount;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     with[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     UINT8 channelCount;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This eliminates sign‐to‐unsigned casts and ensures stored counts are always [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnon‐negative.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Fix gcc_read_client_network_data in libfreerdp/core/gcc.c:[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Declare all new locals immediately after the opening brace:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      BOOL [0m[1;35mgcc_read_client_network_data[0m[1;39m([0m[39mwStream* s, rdpMcs* mcs[0m[1;39m)[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          UINT8  channelCount;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          UINT32 i;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          rdpMcsChannel* channel;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          const size_t blockLength = [0m[1;35mStream_GetRemainingLength[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mWINPR_ASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mWINPR_ASSERT[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmcs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Read into the local `channelCount`, validate, then assign into the struct:[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mblockLength < [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m                   [0m[35m/[0m[39m* need at least [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m byte for count [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m*[0m[35m/[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              return FALSE;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT8[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, channelCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* local count *[0m[35m/[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mchannelCount > CHANNEL_MAX_COUNT[0m[1;39m)[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[1;35mWLog_ERR[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTAG, [0m[32m"Too many client channel definitions: %"[0m[39m PRIu8, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchannelCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              return FALSE;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[39m* ensure enough bytes remain for all definitions: [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcount * [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + the [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbyte we already consumed *[0m[35m/[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mblockLength < [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m + [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mchannelCount * [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              return FALSE;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          mcs->channelCount = channelCount;       [0m[35m/[0m[39m* safe, struct now UINT8 *[0m[35m/[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Loop over channels using the local count and declared loop variable:[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < channelCount; i++[0m[1;39m)[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              channel = &mcs->channels[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[1;35mStream_Read[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, channel->Name, CHANNEL_NAME_LEN + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mmemchr[0m[1;39m([0m[39mchannel->Name, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, CHANNEL_NAME_LEN + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                  return FALSE;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT32[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, channel->options[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              channel->ChannelId = mcs->baseChannelId++;[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return TRUE;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This preserves the original [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m‐byte per‐channel logic and existing error paths, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbut fixes scoping, undeclared identifiers, and unsafe signed casts.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Fix user‐channel parsing in mcs.c [0m[1;39m([0m[39min mcs_recv_connect_initial or the equivalent[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction that reads `userChannelCount`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. At the top of the function [0m[1;39m([0m[39mafter `WINPR_ASSERT` calls[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, declare:[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      UINT8  userChannelCount;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      UINT32 j;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      UINT16 length;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Replace the unguarded reads with:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mber_read_octet_string_tag[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, &length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ||[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          ![0m[1;35mStream_CheckAndLogRequiredLength[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTAG, s, length[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return FALSE;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* read and bound-check the number of channels the client wants to join *[0m[35m/[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;35mStream_Read_UINT8[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, userChannelCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39muserChannelCount > CHANNEL_MAX_COUNT[0m[1;39m)[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mWLog_ERR[0m[1;39m([0m[39mTAG, [0m[32m"Too many user channels to join: %"[0m[39m PRIu8, [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muserChannelCount[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return FALSE;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* invoke conference request for each channel *[0m[35m/[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mj = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; j < userChannelCount; j++[0m[1;39m)[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mgcc_read_conference_create_request[0m[1;39m([0m[39ms, mcs[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              return FALSE;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This ensures `userChannelCount` and `j` are declared and properly scoped, and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39menforces the same `CHANNEL_MAX_COUNT` limit when joining user channels.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Retain existing harness, fuzzing, and test code unchanged:[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All added logic lives in core/gcc.c and core/mcs.c. No modifications to [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mharness or tests are required, so existing tests and fuzzing entries still pass [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munchanged.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Validation and side‐effects:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By using local `UINT8` variables and assigning to the now‐unsigned struct [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfield, negative or overly large counts can no longer slip through via [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msigned‐to‐unsigned conversion.[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The existing per‐channel read logic and block‐length checks remain in place [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand are simply re‐ordered around the new safe‐guard.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The capacity allocated in `mcs_new` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mcalloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCHANNEL_MAX_COUNT, …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msufficient for the enforced limits.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - There is no change to network protocol semantics other than adding an [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mupper‐bound check, so interoperability is preserved.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any future use of `mcs->channelCount` will see only validated, non‐negative [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcounts.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. No external libraries, fuzz harnesses, or tests are touched, preserving build [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand test stability.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
